---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'St Kitts Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/saint-kitts-and-nevis/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Antigua for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/antigua-and-barbuda' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
  { title: 'Bahamas for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahamas' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'stKittsFit', header: 'St Kitts Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,350-1,930/mo', stKittsFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,580-2,255/mo', stKittsFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,215-1,735/mo', stKittsFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,130-1,615/mo', stKittsFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Guardian)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$400-800/mo', stKittsFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'XCD$1,215-1,930', annual: 'XCD$14,580-23,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'XCD$1,665-2,575', annual: 'XCD$19,980-30,900' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'XCD$2,240-3,450', annual: 'XCD$26,880-41,400' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'XCD$250-500/visit', annual: 'As needed' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'XCD$50,000-150,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Saint Kitts and Nevis 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Saint Kitts and Nevis. Original CBI pioneer, twin islands, and coverage for wealthy retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Saint Kitts and Nevis"
  subheadline="Saint Kitts and Nevis offers the original citizenship by investment program, twin-island Caribbean charm, colonial history, and exclusive communities—a prestigious destination for wealthy retirees seeking second citizenship."
  heroImage="/images/countries/saint-kitts-and-nevis-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Saint Kitts and Nevis</h2>
  <p>
    Saint Kitts and Nevis pioneered citizenship by investment in 1984—the world's longest-running CBI program. Offers twin-island experience with Mount Liamuiga volcano, colonial Brimstone Hill fortress, exclusive Nevis communities, and tax-free living. Attracts wealthy retirees seeking prestigious second citizenship.
  </p>

  <p>
    Basseterre (St Kitts) is capital with main services. Frigate Bay has expat communities. Nevis is quieter, more exclusive island. Population ~55,000 total. Puerto Rico is 1.5 hours flight with US healthcare; Miami 3.5 hours.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Puerto Rico/Miami evacuation</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> XCD$7,000-14,000/month (~$2,600-5,200 USD); expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; hurricane zone</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Exclusive; historic; quiet</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax, capital gains, wealth or inheritance tax</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Saint Kitts Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Healthcare is limited—Joseph N. France General Hospital (St Kitts) is main facility. Alexandra Hospital on Nevis is smaller. Limited specialists. Complex cases evacuate to Puerto Rico (1.5 hours, US healthcare) or Miami (3.5 hours). International insurance with US evacuation essential.
  </p>

  <p>
    Puerto Rico provides closest US-quality backup. Some wealthy residents fly to Miami for elective procedures. Private clinics handle routine care. Don't rely on local healthcare for serious senior conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Puerto Rico Backup</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Puerto Rico (US territory) is just 1.5 hours away with US healthcare standards. Closer than Miami for emergencies. Hospital HIMA San Pablo, Centro Cardiovascular provide good care. Ensure insurance covers Puerto Rico and continental US.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Saint Kitts and Nevis residency options:
  </p>

  <h3>Citizenship by Investment (Pioneer)</h3>
  <p>
    World's oldest CBI (since 1984). $250,000+ donation or $400,000+ real estate. St Kitts passport provides visa-free travel to 155+ countries including UK and Schengen.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residency</h3>
  <p>
    Available through investment at lower threshold. Right to live without citizenship passport benefits.
  </p>

  <h3>Nevis Special</h3>
  <p>
    Nevis offers separate residency options as semi-autonomous island. Some prefer quieter Nevis lifestyle.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for St Kitts and Nevis:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Puerto Rico and US coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane:</strong> Northern islands have higher risk</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for St Kitts</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with Puerto Rico and US coverage essential. Local care handles routine needs. Puerto Rico often preferred for emergencies due to proximity. Hurricane evacuation coverage recommended.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in St Kitts and Nevis, US evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for St Kitts</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Americas network, US access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Puerto Rico access:</strong> Closest US healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Premium service:</strong> Match wealthy clientele expectations</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for St Kitts with US evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for St Kitts (XCD ~2.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Premium destination:</strong> Wealthy clientele expect premium coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Tax-free:</strong> No income tax offsets healthcare costs</li>
    <li><strong>US access:</strong> Essential for quality care</li>
    <li><strong>Higher CBI cost:</strong> Most expensive Caribbean citizenship</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: CBI Pioneer, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $8,000/month. Original CBI investor. Frigate Bay residence.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with worldwide coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,900/month (~$700). Premium coverage; global mobility.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Nevis Exclusivity, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $10,000/month. Four Seasons Nevis community. Privacy focused.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global premium tier.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$2,100/month (~$780). Exclusive lifestyle; Puerto Rico backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Tax Optimizer, 65</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $6,000/month. Tax-free living. Basseterre area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Americas coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,400/month (~$520). Tax savings; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why is St Kitts CBI most expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Oldest and most prestigious—35+ year track record. Strongest passport (155+ visa-free countries). Established reputation. Higher price reflects perceived quality and visa-free access to more destinations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">St Kitts vs Nevis—which to choose?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        St Kitts is larger with more services. Nevis is quieter, more exclusive, famous for Four Seasons resort. Nevis attracts ultra-wealthy seeking privacy. St Kitts for practical daily living. Both share citizenship.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Hurricane risk in St Kitts?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate to high—northern Caribbean location. Hurricanes Irma and Maria (2017) caused damage. Proper construction matters. Many residents evacuate during peak hurricane season (Aug-Oct).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What are the complete tax advantages?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Comprehensive—no income tax, no capital gains tax, no wealth tax, no inheritance tax, no gift tax. One of world's most tax-friendly jurisdictions. Professional tax planning essential before relocation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for St Kitts coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Healthcare in St Kitts is limited—US evacuation coverage essential. CBI requirements change. Always verify current requirements with St Kitts authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
